3. OPTIONAL AI MODELS
---------------------

All AI model weights are optional components. An installation may contain
weights previously downloaded by the user or installer, but they are not
covered by the DepthVista XR license. Downloading, storing, or selecting a
model does not change the license of DepthVista XR or its third-party source
code. Each model remains governed exclusively by the license supplied by its
author or distributor.

Some supported models permit commercial use, while others are restricted to
non-commercial use. Model licenses may also differ between sizes, variants,
checkpoints, or repositories belonging to the same model family.

Known examples include:

Depth Anything
  - Depth Anything V1: consult the original repository and checkpoint license.
    https://github.com/LiheYoung/Depth-Anything
  - Depth Anything V2 Small: Apache License 2.0 according to its repository.
  - Depth Anything V2 Base, Large, and Giant: CC BY-NC 4.0 according to its
    repository.
    https://github.com/DepthAnything/Depth-Anything-V2

Video Depth Anything
  - Small: Apache License 2.0 according to its repository.
  - Base and Large: CC BY-NC 4.0 according to its repository.
    https://github.com/DepthAnything/Video-Depth-Anything

Distill Any Depth
  - Consult the repository license and the license of the exact checkpoint.
  - Checkpoints derived from or initialized using restricted model weights
    may retain additional restrictions.
    https://github.com/Westlake-AGI-Lab/Distill-Any-Depth

Depth Anything 3, ZoeDepth, Depth Pro, metric-depth variants, and other
supported models
  - Consult the official repository and the exact checkpoint license before
    downloading, redistributing, or using a model.

This list is informational and is not a substitute for the license shipped
with a specific checkpoint. If this document conflicts with a model author's
license, the model author's license controls for that model.


4. COMMERCIAL USE
-----------------

The fact that DepthVista XR can load an optional non-commercial model does
not make the entire project or all other models non-commercial.

Commercial use must be evaluated separately for:

  1. the original MIT-licensed nunif and xrplay code;
  2. the CC BY-NC 4.0 DepthVista XR additions and modifications;
  3. every optional model and checkpoint selected by the user;
  4. every bundled or dynamically loaded third-party library.

Using a CC BY-NC 4.0 model, such as certain Depth Anything V2 or Video Depth
Anything variants, remains subject to that model's non-commercial
restriction. Removing or not downloading those models does not remove the
separate CC BY-NC 4.0 restriction applying to the original DepthVista XR
material described in Section 1.


5. OTHER THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
-------------------------------

DepthVista XR may use libraries including Dear PyGui, PyTorch, NumPy, Pillow,
OpenCV, PyAV, and FFmpeg. Their respective copyright notices and licenses
apply independently.

In particular, the license obligations of a Windows binary distribution may
differ from those of the Python source code because PyAV or FFmpeg builds can
enable GPL-licensed components. Distributors must inspect the exact binaries
they ship and provide all notices, license texts, and source-code offers
required by those builds.

Common project sources:

  Dear PyGui: https://github.com/hoffstadt/DearPyGui
  PyTorch:    https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch
  NumPy:      https://numpy.org/
  Pillow:     https://python-pillow.org/
  OpenCV:     https://opencv.org/
  PyAV:       https://github.com/PyAV-Org/PyAV
  FFmpeg:     https://ffmpeg.org/


